        "content": "<p>MWE:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">T</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„•</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">T.m</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">x.m.m</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">begin</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">let</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">change</span> <span class=\"n\">x.m</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- T.m y = x</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">refl</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">end</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>After <code>let</code>, but before <code>refl</code>, the goal is displayed as <code>T.m y = x</code> instead of <code>y.m = x</code>. Tactic <code>change y.m = x</code> does not help. Is there a way to force the dot notation? Note that this is just a minimal example. It happened to me in a real proof and the goal became totally unreadable.</p>",
